function.arguments: {"instructions": "What are the seven largest islands in the world, along with the countries they belong to?"}

chat_history.content:
Here are the seven largest islands in the world and the countries they belong to:

1. **Greenland**: 2,130,800 km² (822,700 sq mi) - Part of the Kingdom of Denmark.
2. **New Guinea**: 785,753 km² (303,380 sq mi) - Divided between Papua New Guinea (eastern half) and Indonesia (western half, known as Western New Guinea).
3. **Borneo**: 748,168 km² (288,869 sq mi) - Divided among Malaysia, Brunei, and Indonesia.
4. **Madagascar**: 587,713 km² (226,917 sq mi) - An island country located in the Indian Ocean.
5. **Baffin Island**: 507,451 km² (195,928 sq mi) - Part of Canada, located in the territory of Nunavut.
6. **Sumatra**: 443,066 km² (171,069 sq mi) - Part of Indonesia.
7. **Honshu**: 225,800 km² (87,200 sq mi) - Part of Japan.

These islands are listed in descending order by area.</s>

chat_history.content:
Here are the capital cities of the seven largest islands in the world:

1. **Greenland**:
   - Country: Part of the Kingdom of Denmark
   - Capital: Copenhagen (Denmark)
2. **New Guinea**:
   - Country: Divided between Papua New Guinea (eastern half) and Indonesia (western half)
   - Capitals: Port Moresby (Papua New Guinea), Jakarta (Indonesia)
3. **Borneo**:
   - Country: Divided among Malaysia, Brunei, and Indonesia
   - Capitals: Kuala Lumpur (Malaysia), Bandar Seri Begawan (Brunei), Jakarta (Indonesia)
4. **Madagascar**:
   - Country: Madagascar
   - Capital: Antananarivo
5. **Baffin Island**:
   - Country: Part of Canada
   - Capital: Ottawa (Canada)
6. **Sumatra**:
   - Country: Part of Indonesia
   - Capital: Jakarta (Indonesia)
7. **Honshu**:
   - Country: Part of Japan
   - Capital: Tokyo (Japan)

These islands are listed in descending order by area.

Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

**Port Moresby** (/ˈmɔːrzbi/; Tok Pisin: *Pot Mosbi*), also referred to as **Pom City** or simply **Moresby**, is the capital and largest city of Papua New Guinea. It is one of the largest cities in the southwestern Pacific (along with Jayapura) outside of Australia and New Zealand. It is located on the shores of the Gulf of Papua, on the south-western coast of the Papuan Peninsula of the island of New Guinea. The city emerged as a trade centre in the second half of the 19th century. During World War II, it was a prime objective for conquest by the Imperial Japanese forces during 1942–43 as a staging point and air base to cut off Australia from Southeast Asia and the Americas.

<title>National Capital District (Papua New Guinea)</title>
<fragment>

**The National Capital District** of Papua New Guinea is the incorporated area around Port Moresby, which is the capital of Papua New Guinea. Although it is surrounded by Central Province, where Port Moresby is also the capital, it is technically not a part of that province. It covers an area of 240 km2 and has a population of 364,125 (2011 census).[2][3] It is represented by three open MPs and an NCD-wide representative in the National Parliament of Papua New Guinea who acts as Governor of the National Capital District; however, these MPs do not have the same powers as elsewhere in the country due to the role of the National Capital District Commission.[4]




## Governors

[edit]

The National Capital District did not have a decentralised administration with a Premier, as with the other provinces, prior to 1995; however, since the 1995 reforms of provincial governments it has been headed by a Governor, albeit one with more limited powers.[5]

**Capital punishment** is not a legal punishment in the **Independent State of Papua New Guinea**.


Capital punishment was abolished on 22 January 2022.[1] It was legal under Australian colonial rule, but was abolished in 1970 in the leadup to independence. It was reinstated in 1991, but never used. The last execution was by hanging, in Port Moresby, in November 1954.[2][3]




## History

[edit]

Within the Pacific Islands Forum, all countries (albeit not PNG) have either completely abolished capital punishment or have refrained from imposing it for numerous decades.[4] The use of capital punishment in PNG has fluctuated throughout history and has again become unsettled in recent years.

functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

functions.name: search
functions.desc: Search Wikipedia for an article with the given title, and get its content. If no such article is found, return similar article names.
